WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.987 --> 00:00:05.188
<i>Previously on</i> Marshals...

2
00:00:05.189 --> 00:00:06.791
[Calvin] <i>We got to hold
on what we got.</i>

3
00:00:06.891 --> 00:00:08.192
We don't move.
it's Roner all over.

4
00:00:08.326 --> 00:00:09.693
♪ dramatic music ♪

5
00:00:09.793 --> 00:00:10.861
[Dr. Ginsburg]
<i>Said you'd been experiencing</i>

6
00:00:10.961 --> 00:00:12.663
some neck and shoulder pain?

7
00:00:12.796 --> 00:00:15.299
We'll run some tests.
try to find you some answers.

8
00:00:15.399 --> 00:00:16.634
Would you like to go
on a date sometime?

9
00:00:16.734 --> 00:00:18.034
I'd love to.

10
00:00:18.035 --> 00:00:19.502
Family name doesn't
carry water anymore.

11
00:00:19.503 --> 00:00:21.872
so you got to hide
behind a federal badge?

12
00:00:23.507 --> 00:00:28.279
- [Belle] This... is a terrible idea.
- [chuckles] Long day.

13
00:00:28.379 --> 00:00:30.514
[Belle sighs]

14
00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:38.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

15
00:00:40.458 --> 00:00:42.726
♪ low. dramatic music ♪

16
00:01:06.317 --> 00:01:08.486
♪

17
00:01:11.389 --> 00:01:13.257
[bus door closes]

18
00:01:26.504 --> 00:01:29.172
[Tate sighs]
Winter fields came in nice.

19
00:01:29.273 --> 00:01:32.242
[Kayce] Yeah. Tom Weaver's hands
get all the credit.

20
00:01:32.343 --> 00:01:34.978
His daughter's hands
get credit. too?

21
00:01:35.779 --> 00:01:37.948
Hey. you communicating
with aliens?

22
00:01:38.048 --> 00:01:41.084
'Cause these hay bales
can't be for decoration. right?

23
00:01:41.218 --> 00:01:42.586
They're to feed the herd.

24
00:01:42.686 --> 00:01:44.555
Grass gets scarce
when the snow comes in.

25
00:01:44.655 --> 00:01:47.190
[Tate] Get your hand warmers
ready. city slicker.

26
00:01:47.291 --> 00:01:48.626
Winter's coming.

27
00:01:48.759 --> 00:01:49.827
[Calvin] It's the first time
someone from Omaha's

28
00:01:49.927 --> 00:01:51.362
been slapped with that label.

29
00:01:51.462 --> 00:01:54.698
But I have you know. Tate.
I was freezing my ass off

30
00:01:54.798 --> 00:01:56.766
in the Hindu Kush when you
were still in diapers.

31
00:01:56.767 --> 00:01:57.735
[scoffs]

32
00:01:57.835 --> 00:02:00.638
Supposed to meet up with Deebo.

33
00:02:00.771 --> 00:02:02.573
Unless you got more grass
you want to stare at?

34
00:02:02.673 --> 00:02:05.042
Get out of here.

35
00:02:08.746 --> 00:02:11.482
Man. it's nice to see you two
doing so well.

36
00:02:12.583 --> 00:02:14.318
You know.
being a father suits you.

37
00:02:14.418 --> 00:02:16.454
Didn't come natural.

38
00:02:17.588 --> 00:02:19.457
I thought being somebody's son
would be the hardest thing

39
00:02:19.557 --> 00:02:21.191
I ever had to deal with.

40
00:02:22.660 --> 00:02:27.130
[sighs] Man. I needed a morning
like this. Thank you. Coyo.

41
00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:28.632
Everything good?

42
00:02:28.732 --> 00:02:32.536
Yeah. just fighting battles
on multiple fronts. but

43
00:02:32.636 --> 00:02:34.438
it's nice to know
you got my six.

44
00:02:35.339 --> 00:02:37.841
Sketchy guy coming up
the driveway to the house.

45
00:02:37.975 --> 00:02:39.610
♪ dramatic music ♪

46
00:02:57.628 --> 00:02:59.162
[Kayce]
You lost?

47
00:02:59.262 --> 00:03:02.633
Not if I'm trying to figure out
where all the cowboys have gone.

48
00:03:02.733 --> 00:03:05.167
Think you can back up
that smart talk

49
00:03:05.168 --> 00:03:06.869
armed only with that six string?

50
00:03:06.870 --> 00:03:11.008
Ain't you heard?
I was born dangerous. Coyo.

51
00:03:12.109 --> 00:03:14.177
[scoffs]

52
00:03:14.712 --> 00:03:15.946
[grunts]

53
00:03:19.316 --> 00:03:20.851
Damn. Double G.

54
00:03:20.951 --> 00:03:24.722
- I ain't seen you since...
- Camp Uhley. Afghanistan.

55
00:03:24.855 --> 00:03:26.023
[Kayce]
So. after all this time.

56
00:03:26.123 --> 00:03:27.524
you just figured
you'd show up in Montana

57
00:03:27.525 --> 00:03:28.859
unannounced. huh?

58
00:03:28.992 --> 00:03:31.027
[Garrett] Well.
felt a calling to head west.

59
00:03:31.028 --> 00:03:33.464
see how my old teammate
was doing.

60
00:03:34.432 --> 00:03:36.566
Good Lord. is that Tate?

61
00:03:36.567 --> 00:03:38.135
[Kayce]
Hey. Tate.

62
00:03:38.235 --> 00:03:40.036
I want you to meet Garrett. He's
my old buddy from the Teams.

63
00:03:40.037 --> 00:03:41.539
[Tate]
Figured.

64
00:03:41.639 --> 00:03:44.041
Can't imagine anyone else
getting a greeting like that.

65
00:03:44.174 --> 00:03:46.076
♪ low. dramatic music ♪

66
00:03:47.177 --> 00:03:50.213
Cal? Wasn't expecting
to see you.

67
00:03:50.313 --> 00:03:54.017
Double G. In the flesh.

68
00:03:54.818 --> 00:03:57.821
I guess I should start
believing in ghosts.

69
00:04:00.257 --> 00:04:01.592
You were all teammates?

70
00:04:01.725 --> 00:04:04.061
Three-quarters of a badass group
of pipe hitters

71
00:04:04.161 --> 00:04:06.664
everybody called
the Four Musketeers.

72
00:04:06.764 --> 00:04:08.766
Nobody called us that.

73
00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:10.634
Who's the fourth?

74
00:04:10.734 --> 00:04:13.036
♪ somber music ♪

75
00:04:16.373 --> 00:04:18.075
Let's. uh.
get your stuff inside.

76
00:04:18.175 --> 00:04:19.910
There's a lot to catch up on.
Ain't that right. Cal?

77
00:04:20.043 --> 00:04:24.414
I got something back at work.
It's good seeing you. Double G.

78
00:04:24.515 --> 00:04:25.916
Come on.

79
00:04:26.049 --> 00:04:29.086
Sure thing. boss.

80
00:04:30.053 --> 00:04:31.989
Get you inside. man.

81
00:04:34.057 --> 00:04:36.259
♪ soaring. dynamic music ♪

82
00:05:00.884 --> 00:05:03.020
♪

83
00:05:16.066 --> 00:05:18.636
Hey. The fugitive

84
00:05:18.769 --> 00:05:21.639
we collared yesterday
was processed in Helena.

85
00:05:21.772 --> 00:05:23.541
And?

86
00:05:24.307 --> 00:05:26.376
And I thought
you'd want to know.

87
00:05:26.476 --> 00:05:29.079
Now I do. Thanks.

88
00:05:31.148 --> 00:05:32.349
You feeling okay?

89
00:05:32.482 --> 00:05:34.517
Yeah. yeah. Why wouldn't I be?

90
00:05:34.518 --> 00:05:38.689
Jared said your run-in was at
the doctor's office parking lot.

91
00:05:38.789 --> 00:05:42.491
- You left that detail out.
- I'm fine.

92
00:05:42.492 --> 00:05:44.327
Okay.

93
00:05:48.298 --> 00:05:49.900
Are we?

94
00:05:52.603 --> 00:05:55.305
We both agreed we made
a mistake and. you know.

95
00:05:55.405 --> 00:05:57.474
gonna respect boundaries
at work.

96
00:05:57.575 --> 00:05:59.076
Stay front-sight focused.

97
00:06:01.745 --> 00:06:03.046
It's nothing personal.

98
00:06:03.146 --> 00:06:05.515
Yeah. no. nothing personal.

99
00:06:07.551 --> 00:06:08.852
Right.

100
00:06:11.855 --> 00:06:15.058
[Kayce] Down.
Down. down. down. Good. Good.

101
00:06:15.192 --> 00:06:16.893
[Garrett] That horse has a fire
in his belly.

102
00:06:16.894 --> 00:06:19.196
I'd sooner jump on a grenade
than mess with him.

103
00:06:19.296 --> 00:06:21.464
[Kayce] Yeah.
he's got a temper for sure.

104
00:06:22.365 --> 00:06:24.867
I guess I would too if somebody
was trying to take my freedom.

105
00:06:24.868 --> 00:06:27.537
Well. I wish somebody
would've gave us this much TLC

106
00:06:27.638 --> 00:06:29.206
when we got out of the sandbox.

107
00:06:29.306 --> 00:06:32.576
All right. Come on. Come on.

108
00:06:38.682 --> 00:06:39.883
Good.

109
00:06:43.086 --> 00:06:46.388
I guess nobody gets off easy
getting out of the Teams.

110
00:06:46.389 --> 00:06:48.558
You had it worse than most.

111
00:06:49.793 --> 00:06:51.962
I look like I'm gonna
suck start my pistol to you?

112
00:06:52.062 --> 00:06:54.297
Just haven't seen you
in a decade.

113
00:06:55.298 --> 00:06:57.801
You were spinning out
pretty good last time I did.

114
00:06:58.969 --> 00:07:01.772
I ain't got a worry
in the world. Coyo.

115
00:07:01.872 --> 00:07:04.074
Trading in that rifle
for a guitar

116
00:07:04.207 --> 00:07:05.843
was the best decision
I ever made.

117
00:07:06.576 --> 00:07:09.112
Always did like
hearing you play that thing.

118
00:07:09.212 --> 00:07:12.282
I've been making a name
for myself up in Nashville. too.

119
00:07:14.017 --> 00:07:17.454
Glad you left the past
in the sandbox. brother.

120
00:07:17.554 --> 00:07:19.256
No looking
in the rearview for me.

121
00:07:19.356 --> 00:07:21.424
Music's my purpose.

122
00:07:21.558 --> 00:07:23.994
Seems you and old Cal
found a new one. too.

123
00:07:25.495 --> 00:07:28.231
I was spinning my wheels till
he offered me a Marshal badge.

124
00:07:28.331 --> 00:07:32.135
[scoffs] Ain't that rich.

125
00:07:32.269 --> 00:07:36.239
Cal gives you a new career.
and he ended mine.

126
00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:39.309
♪ somber music ♪

127
00:07:39.442 --> 00:07:42.680
Well. all this reminiscing's
making me thirsty.

128
00:07:55.125 --> 00:07:56.694
- [country music playing]
- Well. you know.

129
00:07:56.794 --> 00:07:59.329
only ten percent of first dates
make it to the third.

130
00:07:59.429 --> 00:08:02.666
Good for us.
beating the odds already.

131
00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:06.236
We got to survive
our fourth date

132
00:08:06.336 --> 00:08:10.340
before "us" makes it
into our vernacular.

133
00:08:10.473 --> 00:08:13.310
Not to get ahead
of anything. but. uh.

134
00:08:13.443 --> 00:08:15.478
are you thinking
about telling Cal?

135
00:08:16.479 --> 00:08:18.682
The man's got no say in my life.

136
00:08:19.482 --> 00:08:21.284
But he does in mine.

137
00:08:24.654 --> 00:08:26.489
Fine. How about now?

138
00:08:31.661 --> 00:08:34.431
- He just walked in. didn't he?
- [Calvin] Wait.

139
00:08:34.531 --> 00:08:36.767
So this is a-a thing?

140
00:08:40.871 --> 00:08:42.773
You got nothing to say?

141
00:08:43.707 --> 00:08:46.710
I didn't realize she was your
daughter when I asked her out.

142
00:08:47.978 --> 00:08:50.013
It's not something
I boast about.

143
00:08:58.288 --> 00:08:59.622
Enjoy your evenings.

144
00:09:09.532 --> 00:09:11.068
That charcoal filter.

145
00:09:11.168 --> 00:09:13.403
that's what makes it
Tennessee whiskey.

146
00:09:13.536 --> 00:09:15.538
Why are you pimping
Tennessee so hard?

147
00:09:15.638 --> 00:09:17.074
You said you were from Alabama.

148
00:09:17.207 --> 00:09:18.876
Well. I am.

149
00:09:18.976 --> 00:09:21.344
Only good thing
to come out of there is I-20.

150
00:09:21.444 --> 00:09:23.246
Myself included.

151
00:09:23.380 --> 00:09:25.547
I had to drag you out here
last week.

152
00:09:25.548 --> 00:09:27.284
now you're just
a regular. cowboy?

153
00:09:27.384 --> 00:09:29.085
I'm just playing tour guide.

154
00:09:29.086 --> 00:09:31.955
Garrett didn't appreciate the
peace and quiet at the ranch.

155
00:09:32.055 --> 00:09:34.091
Ugh. I get it.
I can't wait to get back

156
00:09:34.224 --> 00:09:36.193
to the concrete jungle myself.

157
00:09:36.293 --> 00:09:38.395
Fresh air is too suffocating.

158
00:09:38.495 --> 00:09:40.562
You know. I think you just
gave me my next song title.

159
00:09:40.563 --> 00:09:43.066
And that makes you my muse.

160
00:09:43.166 --> 00:09:44.600
[Kayce] You know.
last time I heard you play.

161
00:09:44.601 --> 00:09:47.104
you were interrupted
by a mortar attack.

162
00:09:47.871 --> 00:09:50.173
Taliban's a tough crowd. huh?

163
00:09:50.273 --> 00:09:51.674
They ain't got nothing
on those dive bars

164
00:09:51.775 --> 00:09:52.843
I've played down south. though.

165
00:09:52.943 --> 00:09:54.244
[Andrea]
The stage is right there.

166
00:09:54.344 --> 00:09:56.245
You can finish
what you started for Kayce.

167
00:09:56.246 --> 00:09:59.415
I only play big venues
now. darling.

168
00:09:59.416 --> 00:10:01.852
[Andrea chuckles]

169
00:10:01.952 --> 00:10:05.622
Hey. Pull up a chair. Cal.
I'm buying.

170
00:10:08.058 --> 00:10:09.793
I think I'm gonna rain check it.

171
00:10:09.927 --> 00:10:11.294
After all we've been through.

172
00:10:11.394 --> 00:10:12.996
you can't sit down.
have one drink with me?

173
00:10:16.699 --> 00:10:18.001
[Calvin]
Yeah. you know what?

174
00:10:18.101 --> 00:10:22.940
Next round. and the round
after that. is on me.

175
00:10:23.040 --> 00:10:24.875
Okay? Enjoy your night.

176
00:10:24.975 --> 00:10:27.110
Hooyah. Senior Chief.

177
00:10:30.180 --> 00:10:33.650
Well. here's to Two Musketeers.

178
00:10:33.750 --> 00:10:35.018
Cheers.

179
00:10:35.118 --> 00:10:36.652
<i>♪ Shake it ♪</i>

180
00:10:36.653 --> 00:10:40.290
<i>♪ Make it till the m-m-morning ♪</i>

181
00:10:40.423 --> 00:10:42.125
[bird cawing]

182
00:10:42.225 --> 00:10:43.492
[door closes]

183
00:10:43.493 --> 00:10:45.162
- [door closes]
- [Calvin] Hey.

184
00:10:45.295 --> 00:10:48.831
Double G have you
howling at the moon last night?

185
00:10:48.832 --> 00:10:52.802
Took all my frogman skills just
to get him out of the Bullet.

186
00:10:52.903 --> 00:10:54.872
How is he?

187
00:10:56.139 --> 00:10:57.941
He's better than I expected.

188
00:10:58.041 --> 00:10:59.910
Seems to be all in
on this music thing.

189
00:11:00.010 --> 00:11:02.312
I mean. if he says so.

190
00:11:03.146 --> 00:11:05.814
Man shows up out of the blue.
after a decade.

191
00:11:05.815 --> 00:11:07.316
'cause life is good?

192
00:11:07.317 --> 00:11:08.651
Come on.

193
00:11:08.751 --> 00:11:10.253
I know a damaged frogman
when I see one.

194
00:11:10.353 --> 00:11:11.488
You should.

195
00:11:12.322 --> 00:11:14.357
You caused a lot of his damage.

196
00:11:21.831 --> 00:11:24.334
[indistinct chatter]

197
00:11:26.870 --> 00:11:29.371
Hey. Tip just came in.

198
00:11:29.372 --> 00:11:32.208
Fugitive on our
Top 15 Most Wanted list.

199
00:11:32.209 --> 00:11:34.811
- Reed Pollard.
- [Calvin] Wait.

200
00:11:34.912 --> 00:11:37.880
The most wanted bank robber of
his generation is in our town?

201
00:11:37.881 --> 00:11:39.548
Planning his next heist.

202
00:11:39.549 --> 00:11:41.351
We got a possible
location on him.

203
00:11:41.451 --> 00:11:43.053
Yeah. I mean. Pollard's
been on the board for years.

204
00:11:43.153 --> 00:11:44.687
No one's come close
to catching him.

205
00:11:44.787 --> 00:11:47.757
Yeah. well. he's never been
on our hunting ground.

206
00:11:48.591 --> 00:11:50.226
Okay. Let's roll him up.

207
00:11:50.227 --> 00:11:51.995
♪ suspenseful. dramatic music ♪

208
00:11:56.300 --> 00:11:58.234
Despite pulling off
some of the biggest heists

209
00:11:58.235 --> 00:12:00.003
of the last decade.
Pollard has managed to stay

210
00:12:00.037 --> 00:12:01.238
one step ahead of the Marshals.

211
00:12:01.371 --> 00:12:02.872
Yeah. this guy's
a modern-day Dillinger.

212
00:12:02.973 --> 00:12:04.908
His scores have netted millions.

213
00:12:05.008 --> 00:12:06.576
So what brings him to Montana?

214
00:12:06.709 --> 00:12:09.711
An anonymous tip says he's in
town scouting his next takedown.

215
00:12:09.712 --> 00:12:12.015
Bagging one of our most wanted.
that'd be a great way

216
00:12:12.115 --> 00:12:13.383
to start this day. y'all.

217
00:12:13.483 --> 00:12:15.085
- What's his target?
- [Andrea] We don't know.

218
00:12:15.185 --> 00:12:17.220
just that he's holed up
at the Ashford Rodeo Grounds.

219
00:12:17.354 --> 00:12:20.423
Rodeos have moved south for the
winter. Place will be deserted.

220
00:12:20.557 --> 00:12:21.824
[Belle]
Great. no civvies.

221
00:12:21.925 --> 00:12:23.593
Should we gear up.
full battle rattle?

222
00:12:23.726 --> 00:12:26.063
Pollard's not one to waste time.
so if he's moving on his target.

223
00:12:26.163 --> 00:12:27.597
I need you and Miles here. quarterbacking.

224
00:12:27.697 --> 00:12:29.732
And. Andrea. you and Kayce.
you roll with me.

225
00:12:29.832 --> 00:12:31.168
Okay? Let's move.

226
00:12:33.770 --> 00:12:35.605
Did we just get benched?

227
00:12:35.738 --> 00:12:38.175
Sure feels like it.

228
00:12:38.275 --> 00:12:39.342
What'd you do?

229
00:12:39.442 --> 00:12:42.512
Nothing. You?

230
00:12:42.612 --> 00:12:44.181
Nothing.

231
00:12:44.281 --> 00:12:45.515
They're kicking doors.

232
00:12:45.615 --> 00:12:48.085
We're gonna get stuck here
doing paperwork.

233
00:12:52.122 --> 00:12:54.124
Nothing personal.

234
00:12:54.257 --> 00:12:56.559
- [cattle lowing]
- ♪ dramatic music ♪

235
00:12:56.659 --> 00:12:57.926
Must have an inside connection

236
00:12:57.927 --> 00:12:59.596
to be holed up
in a place like this.

237
00:12:59.696 --> 00:13:01.264
Guy's stolen millions and
chooses to live like an animal?

238
00:13:01.398 --> 00:13:03.600
Lives like an animal
so he can steal millions.

239
00:13:03.733 --> 00:13:05.268
It's that kind
of discipline is why

240
00:13:05.368 --> 00:13:06.736
no one's come close
to catching him.

241
00:13:06.836 --> 00:13:08.271
[Andrea]
How we want to do this?

242
00:13:08.371 --> 00:13:09.639
[Calvin] Pollard's known
for stealth. not force.

243
00:13:09.772 --> 00:13:11.641
so I think fast and dirty
should do it.

244
00:13:11.774 --> 00:13:13.310
[Kayce]
Any word on his team?

245
00:13:13.443 --> 00:13:17.214
Usually only works with a few.
but n-never the same ones.

246
00:13:17.314 --> 00:13:19.149
Tip might be from
a scorned old crew member

247
00:13:19.282 --> 00:13:20.617
who's come back to haunt him.

248
00:13:20.717 --> 00:13:22.652
- Lot of that going around.
- Hey. Movement.

249
00:13:25.322 --> 00:13:26.323
On me.

250
00:13:26.423 --> 00:13:29.426
♪ tense. suspenseful music ♪

251
00:13:34.631 --> 00:13:36.833
[Andrea]
Federal agents. Show yourself!

252
00:13:38.135 --> 00:13:40.303
[metallic clanging]

253
00:13:51.648 --> 00:13:53.550
♪

254
00:14:07.964 --> 00:14:08.997
Contact rear!

255
00:14:08.998 --> 00:14:10.333
[gunfire]

256
00:14:16.439 --> 00:14:17.474
[grunts]

257
00:14:17.574 --> 00:14:19.076
[Calvin]
Go.

258
00:14:21.344 --> 00:14:23.180
[grunts]

259
00:14:31.188 --> 00:14:33.090
Okay. hold fire.

260
00:14:33.190 --> 00:14:34.857
Check these bodies.

261
00:14:34.957 --> 00:14:36.393
[Kayce]
U.S. Marshal!

262
00:14:40.897 --> 00:14:42.799
[Calvin over comms] <i>Kayce.
none of these guys are Pollard.</i>

263
00:14:42.899 --> 00:14:44.467
<i>It's got to be yours.</i>

264
00:14:57.980 --> 00:14:59.116
[gunfire]

265
00:15:00.217 --> 00:15:02.419
[horses neighing]

266
00:15:20.903 --> 00:15:23.573
[horses neighing]

267
00:15:31.781 --> 00:15:34.384
Okay. Kayce and Andrea
are on the ground. searching.

268
00:15:34.484 --> 00:15:35.885
Where are we on Pollard?

269
00:15:35.985 --> 00:15:37.754
Local PD set up roadblocks.
three-mile perimeter.

270
00:15:37.854 --> 00:15:39.889
- Anything pop?
- [Belle] No hits on the BOLO

271
00:15:39.989 --> 00:15:41.524
or at the perimeter checkpoints.

272
00:15:41.624 --> 00:15:43.125
Kayce says he clipped him.

273
00:15:43.126 --> 00:15:45.262
Have we checked hospitals.
local clinics?

274
00:15:45.395 --> 00:15:47.197
No gunshot wounds reported
anywhere within 30 miles.

275
00:15:47.297 --> 00:15:51.100
Gifford's gonna eat my lunch
if Bozeman PD get this collar.

276
00:15:51.201 --> 00:15:54.803
Did our fairy tipster happen
to come in with any more intel?

277
00:15:54.804 --> 00:15:56.806
He's gone radio silent.

278
00:15:56.906 --> 00:15:58.441
Okay. extend
to a statewide search

279
00:15:58.575 --> 00:16:00.976
'cause Pollard could've
stolen a car. slipped the net.

280
00:16:00.977 --> 00:16:02.612
- We can't lose him.
- [Belle] Did you get anything

281
00:16:02.745 --> 00:16:04.614
from the three dead guys
you dropped?

282
00:16:04.747 --> 00:16:05.915
[Calvin]
Still waiting on local PD

283
00:16:06.015 --> 00:16:07.384
to ID the guys

284
00:16:07.484 --> 00:16:09.719
'cause they were only carrying
guns and zip ties.

285
00:16:09.819 --> 00:16:13.022
[Belle] Zip ties were likely
for hostages on their target.

286
00:16:13.122 --> 00:16:14.491
You may have
put them down right as

287
00:16:14.591 --> 00:16:15.825
they were launching their heist.

288
00:16:15.958 --> 00:16:17.326
Didn't put 'em all down.

289
00:16:17.327 --> 00:16:19.995
Yeah. don't remind me. [scoffs]

290
00:16:19.996 --> 00:16:21.564
And Pollard's the headliner
of this crew.

291
00:16:21.664 --> 00:16:25.133
It's unlike this team
to let such a big fish get away.

292
00:16:25.134 --> 00:16:26.802
Kicked the door
with a full unit.

293
00:16:26.803 --> 00:16:28.004
might've turned out different.

294
00:16:28.104 --> 00:16:30.640
Or maybe one of you
catches a round.

295
00:16:31.774 --> 00:16:33.343
You questioning my call?

296
00:16:33.443 --> 00:16:37.314
Not your call. your motive.

297
00:16:38.215 --> 00:16:40.482
My motive is to do
what's best for my team.

298
00:16:40.483 --> 00:16:42.485
and if you feel differently.

299
00:16:42.585 --> 00:16:44.254
that's on you.

300
00:16:45.021 --> 00:16:47.624
Now. we have a fugitive
on the loose.

301
00:16:49.025 --> 00:16:50.893
So. find him.

302
00:16:54.163 --> 00:16:55.298
Hey.

303
00:17:01.471 --> 00:17:03.840
Are you part
of this whole conspiracy?

304
00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:05.242
Oh. no. Man. no.

305
00:17:05.342 --> 00:17:08.845
The conspiracy to sideline me.
that's all you.

306
00:17:08.945 --> 00:17:12.749
I'm talking about
Miles and Maddie.

307
00:17:14.584 --> 00:17:18.387
They're... dating.
or whatever people do nowadays.

308
00:17:18.388 --> 00:17:21.390
Maddie's the girl
Miles had a crush on?

309
00:17:21.391 --> 00:17:25.127
Oh. Well. that explains
your grumpiness.

310
00:17:25.928 --> 00:17:27.264
At least towards him.

311
00:17:27.364 --> 00:17:28.898
Dating somebody I work with.

312
00:17:28.998 --> 00:17:30.533
Maddie's sticking it
to me. right?

313
00:17:30.633 --> 00:17:34.937
Sorry. it's... it's not
respecting work boundaries.

314
00:17:36.439 --> 00:17:38.575
Stay front-sight focused.

315
00:17:42.812 --> 00:17:44.080
[engine revving]

316
00:17:44.213 --> 00:17:46.082
Awful lot of firepower
Pollard's crew

317
00:17:46.215 --> 00:17:49.319
was packing today.
Not his M.O.

318
00:17:49.419 --> 00:17:51.588
He uses different tactics
for pulling off a heist

319
00:17:51.721 --> 00:17:53.055
and keeping his freedom.

320
00:17:53.189 --> 00:17:56.125
Man isn't willing to go quietly.
He made his choice.

321
00:17:56.225 --> 00:17:57.927
He got shot for it.

322
00:17:58.060 --> 00:18:00.029
Allegedly.

323
00:18:01.163 --> 00:18:02.231
I hit him.

324
00:18:03.032 --> 00:18:05.601
So in addition to your
SEAL and cowboy skills.

325
00:18:05.602 --> 00:18:07.370
you're also telepathic?

326
00:18:07.470 --> 00:18:10.238
Okay. who am I gonna
ask you about next?

327
00:18:10.239 --> 00:18:11.408
If you mention Dolly Weaver.

328
00:18:11.541 --> 00:18:13.443
- you're walking home.
- [chuckles]

329
00:18:14.877 --> 00:18:17.747
Is that who has you checking
your phone every ten seconds?

330
00:18:18.748 --> 00:18:21.618
Garrett. actually.
He's not responding.

331
00:18:21.751 --> 00:18:23.952
Oh. he's probably just
sleeping it off.

332
00:18:23.953 --> 00:18:26.723
He was hitting it
pretty hard last night.

333
00:18:27.557 --> 00:18:29.526
[phone buzzing]

334
00:18:30.527 --> 00:18:34.764
911 reports an intruder
in a shed at 533 Marigold Road.

335
00:18:34.897 --> 00:18:36.966
That's four blocks
from the rodeo grounds.

336
00:18:37.767 --> 00:18:39.001
Told you I hit him.

337
00:18:40.370 --> 00:18:42.104
We'll see. cowboy.

338
00:18:42.204 --> 00:18:44.341
♪ suspenseful. dramatic music ♪

339
00:19:08.798 --> 00:19:10.367
He's dead.

340
00:19:17.139 --> 00:19:18.775
That isn't Pollard.

341
00:19:28.951 --> 00:19:30.653
Dead guy Kayce and Andrea
found is Jack Manning

342
00:19:30.787 --> 00:19:33.690
from Pullman. Washington.
No priors.

343
00:19:33.823 --> 00:19:35.658
no known connection to Pollard.

344
00:19:35.792 --> 00:19:37.360
Okay. Where are we
with the rest of the crew?

345
00:19:37.494 --> 00:19:40.196
Troy Ryan. Kenny Roman.
Sam Harold.

346
00:19:40.296 --> 00:19:42.331
Ryan and Roman. both from Iowa.

347
00:19:42.432 --> 00:19:44.100
Harold from rural Michigan.

348
00:19:44.200 --> 00:19:46.002
And according to the FBI.

349
00:19:46.102 --> 00:19:48.337
none are known associates
to Pollard.

350
00:19:48.438 --> 00:19:49.706
[Andrea]
Well. tough luck

351
00:19:49.806 --> 00:19:51.373
running into us on their
first time out with him.

352
00:19:51.374 --> 00:19:54.711
First time out anywhere.
They all have clean jackets.

353
00:19:54.844 --> 00:19:56.546
Clean jackets
don't mean clean living.

354
00:19:56.646 --> 00:19:58.080
True. but this ain't the crew

355
00:19:58.180 --> 00:19:59.849
that pulled off
the Lufthansa heist.

356
00:19:59.949 --> 00:20:01.384
Four strangers

357
00:20:01.518 --> 00:20:04.320
from out of state
with no criminal records.

358
00:20:04.421 --> 00:20:06.355
What are they doing in Montana?

359
00:20:06.489 --> 00:20:08.425
And where is Pollard
in all this?

360
00:20:08.525 --> 00:20:10.292
Could've been nearby when
you got the drop on his guys.

361
00:20:10.393 --> 00:20:11.628
slipped away.

362
00:20:11.728 --> 00:20:14.497
Or maybe he planned the job.
hired a crew

363
00:20:14.597 --> 00:20:16.365
while he stays in the shadows.

364
00:20:16.466 --> 00:20:18.501
Then who tipped us off
that he's in Bozeman?

365
00:20:18.601 --> 00:20:19.769
Wait. can we trace that tip that

366
00:20:19.869 --> 00:20:20.903
led us to Pollard
in the first place?

367
00:20:21.003 --> 00:20:22.237
It came from a burner phone.

368
00:20:22.238 --> 00:20:24.206
It's no longer pinging.

369
00:20:25.007 --> 00:20:27.576
I mean. Pollard's M.O.
has always been hands-on.

370
00:20:27.577 --> 00:20:28.945
so I know he's close by.

371
00:20:30.079 --> 00:20:32.214
We got to flip these four worlds
upside down.

372
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:34.617
Maybe something will pop.
put us on to his whereabouts.

373
00:20:34.717 --> 00:20:37.554
And if he's the mastermind here.
then he armed these guys.

374
00:20:37.654 --> 00:20:39.555
Ballistics on the gun
might tell us a different story.

375
00:20:39.556 --> 00:20:40.957
Yeah. that's good thinking.

376
00:20:41.057 --> 00:20:42.659
Miles. Belle. you keep
digging into this crew.

377
00:20:42.759 --> 00:20:43.760
Let's get those
recovered weapons

378
00:20:43.860 --> 00:20:45.094
over to the ballistics lab.

379
00:20:56.305 --> 00:20:57.640
Where'd Kayce go. by the way?

380
00:20:57.740 --> 00:20:59.909
Said he needed to go
check on Garrett.

381
00:21:00.009 --> 00:21:01.242
Is something wrong?

382
00:21:01.243 --> 00:21:03.345
Couldn't get ahold of him.

383
00:21:06.415 --> 00:21:08.585
What is up with you
and Double G?

384
00:21:08.685 --> 00:21:10.086
He seems like a great guy.

385
00:21:10.186 --> 00:21:12.254
I thought the brotherhood
bonded you for life?

386
00:21:13.856 --> 00:21:15.992
Get these to the lab. okay?

387
00:21:17.126 --> 00:21:19.128
[quietly] Oh. damn it.

388
00:21:19.228 --> 00:21:20.629
What's up?

389
00:21:20.630 --> 00:21:22.331
Look. there's. um. there's
something I forgot to do.

390
00:21:22.431 --> 00:21:24.132
Can you make this run solo?

391
00:21:24.133 --> 00:21:27.136
If it spares me your
yacht rock playlist. I got it.

392
00:21:27.236 --> 00:21:30.139
Look. and hey. make sure
they expedite the tests.

393
00:21:30.272 --> 00:21:32.241
- Okay?
- Hooyah. Senior Chief.

394
00:21:32.341 --> 00:21:34.711
[door opens]

395
00:21:34.811 --> 00:21:36.479
[door closes]

396
00:21:43.753 --> 00:21:45.955
[Garrett mumbling]
Roner.

397
00:21:46.055 --> 00:21:47.289
Roner!

398
00:21:47.389 --> 00:21:48.957
♪ tense. dramatic music ♪

399
00:21:48.958 --> 00:21:51.628
Roner. I'm coming.

400
00:21:54.497 --> 00:21:55.998
Roner. I got you.

401
00:21:56.132 --> 00:21:57.967
- [Kayce] Hey.
- [Garrett] Coming. Roner.

402
00:21:58.067 --> 00:21:59.101
- Garrett.
- I'm coming.

403
00:21:59.201 --> 00:22:01.303
Hey. you're good.
Garrett. Hey.

404
00:22:01.403 --> 00:22:02.639
[gasps]
Get off me. Get off me.

405
00:22:02.739 --> 00:22:04.240
- Get off me.
- [both grunting]

406
00:22:04.340 --> 00:22:06.709
- Garrett.
- Get off me.

407
00:22:08.077 --> 00:22:10.512
- Get off...
- Hey. Garrett.

408
00:22:10.513 --> 00:22:12.148
Garrett. you're good.
It's Coyo.

409
00:22:12.248 --> 00:22:14.817
Hey. It's Coyo. You're good.
You're good.

410
00:22:14.917 --> 00:22:18.154
Hey. hey. you're good. Hey. Hey.

411
00:22:18.254 --> 00:22:21.924
Hey. Hey. Yeah.
You're all right.

412
00:22:22.024 --> 00:22:24.393
Yeah. You're all right.

413
00:22:24.493 --> 00:22:27.129
You're all right. dude. Come on.

414
00:22:27.229 --> 00:22:29.298
[panting]
You're good.

415
00:22:29.398 --> 00:22:31.534
You're good. You're good.

416
00:22:32.802 --> 00:22:34.103
[groans softly]

417
00:22:34.203 --> 00:22:35.837
Still not able to link
any of the shooters

418
00:22:35.838 --> 00:22:36.973
with Pollard or each other.

419
00:22:37.073 --> 00:22:39.408
No texts. emails. calls.

420
00:22:39.508 --> 00:22:41.210
I'm coming up empty myself.

421
00:22:41.343 --> 00:22:45.513
I can't even find evidence
that they were casing a target.

422
00:22:45.514 --> 00:22:47.016
I don't think failing Cal's

423
00:22:47.116 --> 00:22:48.851
gonna get me back
in his good graces.

424
00:22:48.951 --> 00:22:51.954
Sounds like you're at least
winning in your love life.

425
00:22:52.889 --> 00:22:54.691
- He told you about Maddie.
- Mm.

426
00:22:54.824 --> 00:22:56.191
How pissed is he?

427
00:22:56.192 --> 00:22:59.862
I wouldn't say
he's doing cartwheels over it.

428
00:23:02.131 --> 00:23:03.532
Story of my life.

429
00:23:03.666 --> 00:23:05.401
Good thing's always followed
by a bad one.

430
00:23:05.534 --> 00:23:09.405
[sighs] Miles. you liked a girl.
you asked her out.

431
00:23:09.538 --> 00:23:11.440
she said yes.

432
00:23:12.308 --> 00:23:14.310
It's all good.

433
00:23:14.410 --> 00:23:16.212
No. it's not.

434
00:23:16.312 --> 00:23:20.549
My personal life's complicating
my relationship with my boss.

435
00:23:22.218 --> 00:23:23.586
Yeah.

436
00:23:23.720 --> 00:23:28.256
Well. I'm sure
it'll be awkward for a bit.

437
00:23:28.257 --> 00:23:30.026
but it'll blow over.

438
00:23:30.126 --> 00:23:34.931
Just when I started feeling like
I belonged at this job. now...

439
00:23:35.031 --> 00:23:38.801
Cal is only upset
because Maddie is into you.

440
00:23:38.901 --> 00:23:43.271
and she has been keeping him at
arm's length since he got here.

441
00:23:43.272 --> 00:23:44.773
[sighs]

442
00:23:44.774 --> 00:23:47.610
Wait. how long have you known
Maddie's his daughter?

443
00:23:48.110 --> 00:23:49.779
Got some personal details there?

444
00:23:49.879 --> 00:23:53.515
No. I was just assuming things
aren't great with Cal

445
00:23:53.616 --> 00:23:55.985
because he had us going
to his daughter's bar

446
00:23:56.118 --> 00:23:57.654
without sharing why.

447
00:24:00.522 --> 00:24:02.959
We should get back to Pollard.

448
00:24:08.898 --> 00:24:10.466
[door creaks open]

449
00:24:10.566 --> 00:24:11.868
[door closes]

450
00:24:17.974 --> 00:24:19.709
I'll clear out now.

451
00:24:20.509 --> 00:24:22.044
Get out of your hair.

452
00:24:24.947 --> 00:24:27.183
Sorry for the trouble. [sighs]

453
00:24:30.653 --> 00:24:33.690
We're all haunted by what
we did outside the wire.

454
00:24:35.191 --> 00:24:36.726
Or didn't do.

455
00:24:37.894 --> 00:24:40.495
You know. it's pretty twisted
how much more sense life makes

456
00:24:40.496 --> 00:24:43.299
in a war zone
than in the civilized world.

457
00:24:44.667 --> 00:24:47.336
I thought music
was your new purpose

458
00:24:47.436 --> 00:24:50.006
and you're out
doing what you love.

459
00:24:51.674 --> 00:24:54.744
Stopped doing what I love when
I got kicked out of the Teams.

460
00:24:56.879 --> 00:25:00.449
I used to be a part
of an elite combat unit.

461
00:25:00.549 --> 00:25:02.518
Now. I'm...

462
00:25:02.618 --> 00:25:07.589
scrounging for gigs up and down
the Honky Tonk Highway. and...

463
00:25:07.690 --> 00:25:09.125
grown tired of it.

464
00:25:09.692 --> 00:25:12.261
Man. they outed
all the quitters in BUD/S.

465
00:25:13.129 --> 00:25:15.031
You dragging
that guitar around tells me

466
00:25:15.131 --> 00:25:16.866
you're still in the fight.

467
00:25:18.467 --> 00:25:20.770
Music's my only escape.

468
00:25:20.870 --> 00:25:23.305
My only healthy one anyway.

469
00:25:24.073 --> 00:25:28.044
Yeah. when I'm on the stage.
that adrenaline. it...

470
00:25:28.177 --> 00:25:29.746
it helps me forget
about the past.

471
00:25:29.879 --> 00:25:32.581
but as soon as
the applause dies down...

472
00:25:33.883 --> 00:25:36.018
...I say good night to the sun.

473
00:25:36.819 --> 00:25:39.756
♪ somber music ♪

474
00:25:39.889 --> 00:25:42.224
Things got pretty dark
for you. huh?

475
00:25:45.061 --> 00:25:46.595
In and out of jail.

476
00:25:47.663 --> 00:25:50.967
Psych wards. rehab.
sleeping on the streets.

477
00:25:51.067 --> 00:25:52.935
[sighs]

478
00:25:53.035 --> 00:25:55.371
That last op changed everything.

479
00:25:56.739 --> 00:25:58.040
Yeah.

480
00:25:59.241 --> 00:26:01.210
For all four of us.

481
00:26:04.046 --> 00:26:06.248
You've taken
your hits. man. but...

482
00:26:07.549 --> 00:26:09.485
...you're a survivor.

483
00:26:11.353 --> 00:26:14.656
I feel like surviving's
my punishment for what I did.

484
00:26:16.425 --> 00:26:17.927
You may have a lot of demons.

485
00:26:18.027 --> 00:26:20.162
but don't go fighting
for something you didn't earn.

486
00:26:23.032 --> 00:26:25.367
We both know
who Roner's death is on.

487
00:26:27.503 --> 00:26:29.638
I'm trying to
get my head right. Coyo.

488
00:26:30.807 --> 00:26:32.474
I'm losing hope.

489
00:26:37.579 --> 00:26:40.616
I've dealt with a lot of hurt
and loss myself.

490
00:26:42.484 --> 00:26:44.586
This ranch helps.

491
00:26:45.387 --> 00:26:50.026
I may sing country.
but I ain't no cowboy.

492
00:26:50.126 --> 00:26:53.830
The healing power of nature.
that's-that's a real thing.

493
00:26:53.963 --> 00:26:57.299
Being out on the land.

494
00:26:57.433 --> 00:26:59.501
feel a part of it.

495
00:27:02.872 --> 00:27:04.073
It's been a long time

496
00:27:04.173 --> 00:27:06.342
since I felt like
I was a part of anything.

497
00:27:07.309 --> 00:27:08.777
Stay here.

498
00:27:09.611 --> 00:27:12.480
Long as you need until you

499
00:27:12.481 --> 00:27:14.984
find a path forward.

500
00:27:15.117 --> 00:27:17.686
♪ hopeful music ♪

501
00:27:17.786 --> 00:27:20.122
You sure about that?

502
00:27:20.222 --> 00:27:21.824
I mean. I'm-I'm
a lot more complicated

503
00:27:21.958 --> 00:27:23.492
than that ornery horse.

504
00:27:26.996 --> 00:27:29.398
We might not be teammates
anymore.

505
00:27:30.699 --> 00:27:32.701
We're still brothers.

506
00:27:40.009 --> 00:27:41.443
I know it's a lot to take in.

507
00:27:42.244 --> 00:27:43.712
[fading] I'll loop in
a couple of specialists

508
00:27:43.846 --> 00:27:45.714
who have experience
with these kinds of cases.

509
00:27:45.814 --> 00:27:48.784
It's important
to know that you're not alone.

510
00:27:48.885 --> 00:27:51.487
Support groups can provide
a source of stability.

511
00:27:51.587 --> 00:27:53.355
especially early on...

512
00:27:56.225 --> 00:28:00.396
[rap music playing
over car stereo]

513
00:28:00.496 --> 00:28:01.898
[sighs]

514
00:28:01.998 --> 00:28:04.699
[woman rapping indistinctly]

515
00:28:04.700 --> 00:28:05.801
[station changes]

516
00:28:05.902 --> 00:28:07.904
<i>♪ Wanted your love ♪</i>

517
00:28:08.004 --> 00:28:10.039
<i>♪ But all you ever wanted ♪</i>

518
00:28:10.139 --> 00:28:13.409
<i>♪ Is someone to touch... ♪</i>

519
00:28:17.379 --> 00:28:20.249
[GPS voice]
<i>Turn left in 400 feet.</i>

520
00:28:20.349 --> 00:28:24.220
Left ahead?
I already made two lefts.

521
00:28:24.320 --> 00:28:25.487
[engine revving]

522
00:28:26.255 --> 00:28:29.257
[horn blaring]

523
00:28:29.258 --> 00:28:31.893
[country music
continues playing faintly]

524
00:28:31.894 --> 00:28:34.830
♪ ominous music ♪

525
00:28:39.335 --> 00:28:40.869
Mm. Hey.

526
00:28:40.970 --> 00:28:42.438
You didn't respond to my texts.

527
00:28:42.571 --> 00:28:44.440
Uh. I got sidetracked.

528
00:28:44.540 --> 00:28:47.409
Well. we didn't.
We located Pollard.

529
00:28:47.509 --> 00:28:48.744
Where was he hiding out?

530
00:28:48.844 --> 00:28:51.780
A jail in Las Cruces.

531
00:28:51.914 --> 00:28:53.249
New Mexico?

532
00:28:53.349 --> 00:28:56.452
Got picked up five days ago
under an alias.

533
00:28:56.552 --> 00:28:58.955
Small-town cops.
it took them a minute to realize

534
00:28:59.088 --> 00:28:59.989
they had bagged a whale.

535
00:29:00.089 --> 00:29:01.290
Why would someone tip us off

536
00:29:01.390 --> 00:29:03.592
about a fugitive
a thousand miles away?

537
00:29:03.692 --> 00:29:06.062
And Las Cruces cops say
they found nothing on Pollard

538
00:29:06.162 --> 00:29:09.031
pointing to any jobs in Montana.

539
00:29:09.865 --> 00:29:11.500
Did anything pop
on the rest of the crew?

540
00:29:11.600 --> 00:29:14.403
Still hard to figure out
what brought them here.

541
00:29:14.503 --> 00:29:18.975
and no evidence that they were
casing any spots for a heist.

542
00:29:20.242 --> 00:29:22.311
This is starting to feel
like a setup.

543
00:29:22.444 --> 00:29:25.981
Wait. did forensics get back
on the ETA with these results?

544
00:29:25.982 --> 00:29:27.448
No. nothing yet.

545
00:29:27.449 --> 00:29:29.485
Wh... I thought you and Andrea
were doing that together.

546
00:29:30.652 --> 00:29:32.788
Yeah. I to... I mean.
I told you. I got sidetracked.

547
00:29:32.888 --> 00:29:34.123
By what?

548
00:29:34.223 --> 00:29:38.460
Um... Just. uh.
get-get a sitrep from her.

549
00:29:46.302 --> 00:29:48.137
[footsteps approaching]

550
00:29:49.738 --> 00:29:52.174
- Hey.
- Hey.

551
00:29:53.809 --> 00:29:55.944
Taking on one of those
battles you mentioned?

552
00:29:56.745 --> 00:30:00.916
Nah. I was just trying
to figure out if Pollard was.

553
00:30:01.017 --> 00:30:03.651
you know.
some kind of bait for us.

554
00:30:03.652 --> 00:30:05.653
You know?

555
00:30:05.654 --> 00:30:07.623
How's. uh. Garrett?

556
00:30:08.524 --> 00:30:11.593
He's still carrying a lot
of baggage. You were right.

557
00:30:12.794 --> 00:30:14.030
How bad?

558
00:30:14.696 --> 00:30:18.367
Sounds like he's gone Winchester
in his fight to keep going.

559
00:30:19.535 --> 00:30:21.502
And away from the chaos.
you know.

560
00:30:21.503 --> 00:30:23.704
these demons in your head.
they just

561
00:30:23.705 --> 00:30:25.141
keep grinding you down.

562
00:30:25.241 --> 00:30:26.742
especially if you don't got
teammates to lean on.

563
00:30:26.842 --> 00:30:28.044
[Kayce]
Mm-hmm.

564
00:30:28.144 --> 00:30:30.212
And taking his bird
will do that.

565
00:30:30.312 --> 00:30:33.982
I tried everything.
everything. to avoid that.

566
00:30:35.517 --> 00:30:37.352
He's gonna stay with me
for a while.

567
00:30:37.353 --> 00:30:39.388
see if he can sort
some stuff out.

568
00:30:39.488 --> 00:30:40.856
You sure that's a good idea?

569
00:30:40.956 --> 00:30:43.225
Is "no man left behind"
not a thing for you?

570
00:30:43.359 --> 00:30:45.127
You know. he's my brother.
too. Coyo.

571
00:30:45.227 --> 00:30:48.864
And as his team leader. I feel
responsible for his struggles.

572
00:30:48.964 --> 00:30:52.234
but we both know
how combustible Double G is.

573
00:30:53.135 --> 00:30:55.404
I just don't want you
in his blast radius.

574
00:30:56.638 --> 00:30:58.906
It feels like we lost
two brothers on that op.

575
00:30:58.907 --> 00:31:00.942
[footsteps approaching]

576
00:31:03.645 --> 00:31:04.913
- Hey.
- Hey. [sighs]

577
00:31:05.013 --> 00:31:06.582
[Calvin]
You heard back from Andrea?

578
00:31:06.715 --> 00:31:09.318
She's not answering her phone.
and the forensics lab said

579
00:31:09.418 --> 00:31:11.153
she never dropped
the weapons off.

580
00:31:11.587 --> 00:31:13.855
Miles is trying to get
a hit on her SUV.

581
00:31:13.955 --> 00:31:16.992
She should've been
there and back by now.

582
00:31:17.093 --> 00:31:19.260
[Calvin]
Miles. what do you got?

583
00:31:19.261 --> 00:31:21.730
Sheriff found
Andrea's vehicle two miles

584
00:31:21.830 --> 00:31:23.432
- from the lab. smashed up.
- [Calvin] What?

585
00:31:23.565 --> 00:31:25.534
- Is she okay?
- [Miles] There's blood

586
00:31:25.634 --> 00:31:27.236
in the vehicle.
but she wasn't on scene.

587
00:31:27.336 --> 00:31:28.604
What'd she hit?

588
00:31:28.737 --> 00:31:31.340
Truck hit her. broadside.
but it was also empty.

589
00:31:31.440 --> 00:31:32.741
Could be a hit-and-run.

590
00:31:32.874 --> 00:31:34.743
[Calvin]
Did she run. too?

591
00:31:34.843 --> 00:31:37.413
Maybe she was in shock?
Wandered off.

592
00:31:37.546 --> 00:31:41.150
Or a Good Samaritan passed by
and took them all to a hospital.

593
00:31:41.250 --> 00:31:43.619
First we get ambushed
at the rodeo.

594
00:31:43.752 --> 00:31:45.087
now Andrea's missing?

595
00:31:45.221 --> 00:31:46.722
Feels coordinated.

596
00:31:46.822 --> 00:31:48.890
- DUSTWUN.
- [Belle] What does that mean?

597
00:31:48.990 --> 00:31:50.592
Whereabouts unknown.

598
00:31:50.692 --> 00:31:52.760
Sheriff just sent over
traffic cam footage.

599
00:31:52.761 --> 00:31:54.795
All right.
Throw it up on the screen.

600
00:31:54.796 --> 00:31:56.098
♪ suspenseful. dramatic music ♪

601
00:31:56.232 --> 00:31:58.100
[Miles]
There she is.

602
00:32:04.806 --> 00:32:06.775
[Miles]
That's no accident.

603
00:32:06.908 --> 00:32:08.477
[Kayce]
Smash-and-grab.

604
00:32:08.610 --> 00:32:10.778
Classic ambush technique.

605
00:32:10.779 --> 00:32:12.514
My God.

606
00:32:13.415 --> 00:32:14.649
[Miles]
She's not moving.

607
00:32:14.650 --> 00:32:16.017
Yeah.

608
00:32:16.118 --> 00:32:17.786
Impact probably knocked her out.

609
00:32:20.122 --> 00:32:23.324
Okay. Okay. listen up. Hey!

610
00:32:23.325 --> 00:32:25.026
Hey. listen up!

611
00:32:25.927 --> 00:32:28.864
Deputy Marshal Andrea Cruz
has been abducted.

612
00:32:28.964 --> 00:32:30.499
So. whatever you're doing.

613
00:32:30.599 --> 00:32:32.633
getting her back
is our only priority.

614
00:32:32.634 --> 00:32:35.003
Okay? So you track her van.

615
00:32:35.103 --> 00:32:37.038
you ping her phone.
you do whatever it takes.

616
00:32:37.139 --> 00:32:39.475
Okay? No one's taking a break
till she gets back safe.

617
00:32:39.608 --> 00:32:41.008
No one. Let's go.

618
00:32:41.009 --> 00:32:43.044
Get to work!

619
00:32:44.746 --> 00:32:47.316
Hey. who the hell's
coming after us?

620
00:32:47.449 --> 00:32:50.051
Whoever it is.
it feels personal.

621
00:33:08.204 --> 00:33:10.138
[Andrea grunting]

622
00:33:14.876 --> 00:33:18.380
- Help! Help! [groaning]
- [Taser buzzing]

623
00:33:18.514 --> 00:33:20.416
- Behave.
- [Andrea cries out]

624
00:33:20.516 --> 00:33:23.352
[panting. sobbing]

625
00:33:32.461 --> 00:33:35.631
[Andrea groaning]

626
00:33:35.731 --> 00:33:38.233
Help! Help!

627
00:33:38.234 --> 00:33:39.567
[grunts]

628
00:33:39.568 --> 00:33:40.902
[coughs]

629
00:33:41.002 --> 00:33:44.206
Yell all you want.
No one's around to hear you.

630
00:33:44.306 --> 00:33:45.774
[Andrea panting]

631
00:33:45.874 --> 00:33:47.676
[gasping]

632
00:33:47.776 --> 00:33:49.245
Stay there.

633
00:33:52.348 --> 00:33:53.881
Hey. Any luck
tracking her phone?

634
00:33:53.882 --> 00:33:55.284
[Belle]
Been trying to ping it.

635
00:33:55.384 --> 00:33:57.986
It's either turned off
or destroyed.

636
00:33:59.355 --> 00:34:01.389
Road weather cam
a few miles from the accident

637
00:34:01.390 --> 00:34:03.459
caught a cargo van
matching our BOLO.

638
00:34:03.559 --> 00:34:04.860
Okay. it's got to be
the same one.

639
00:34:04.960 --> 00:34:06.328
[Miles]
Got a hit on the registration.

640
00:34:06.428 --> 00:34:08.664
It's a business.
Treasure State Demolition.

641
00:34:09.431 --> 00:34:12.301
That's the first thing
that's made sense all day.

642
00:34:14.536 --> 00:34:16.438
[Andrea panting]

643
00:34:16.538 --> 00:34:19.741
♪ tense. suspenseful music ♪

644
00:34:19.841 --> 00:34:23.144
[man]
Deputy U.S. Marshal Andrea Cruz.

645
00:34:24.079 --> 00:34:25.814
In my home.

646
00:34:27.616 --> 00:34:29.418
What an honor.

647
00:34:29.518 --> 00:34:32.120
[Andrea] Full force of the U.S.
government will be coming for me

648
00:34:32.254 --> 00:34:34.490
and you for breaking the law.

649
00:34:38.694 --> 00:34:40.261
Randall Clegg.

650
00:34:40.262 --> 00:34:44.266
After what your team
has done to my family.

651
00:34:44.366 --> 00:34:47.936
the only law that concerns me
is an eye for an eye.

652
00:34:52.441 --> 00:34:54.643
- [Andrea whimpering]
- [man] Stand up.

653
00:34:59.815 --> 00:35:02.884
Let's prep for a full assault
on Randall Clegg's compound.

654
00:35:04.252 --> 00:35:05.687
Would he grab Andrea
and take her

655
00:35:05.787 --> 00:35:07.154
to the first place we'd look?

656
00:35:07.155 --> 00:35:08.457
Even if she's not there.

657
00:35:08.557 --> 00:35:10.292
somebody on that property
will know something.

658
00:35:10.426 --> 00:35:13.794
What are the protocols
for an abducted U.S. Marshal?

659
00:35:13.795 --> 00:35:15.996
Tear Montana apart
till we find our teammate.

660
00:35:15.997 --> 00:35:19.100
I got a call into Gifford.
It's all hands on deck.

661
00:35:19.501 --> 00:35:21.603
[Miles]
What the hell is Clegg doing?

662
00:35:21.703 --> 00:35:23.171
Getting payback.

663
00:35:23.305 --> 00:35:25.341
Those zip ties we recovered
off the gunmen at the rodeo.

664
00:35:25.441 --> 00:35:26.675
they must've been meant for us.

665
00:35:26.808 --> 00:35:29.345
Going after Kayce's job
is one thing.

666
00:35:29.445 --> 00:35:33.348
but kidnapping a U.S. Marshal?
Why now?

667
00:35:33.349 --> 00:35:34.983
His business went bust.

668
00:35:35.083 --> 00:35:36.652
He lost the rare earth mine
demo contracts

669
00:35:36.785 --> 00:35:39.020
after his sons
shot up Broken Rock.

670
00:35:39.120 --> 00:35:41.690
With one son dead and another
one facing life in prison.

671
00:35:41.823 --> 00:35:42.824
he's got nothing to lose.

672
00:35:42.924 --> 00:35:45.226
♪ tense. dramatic music ♪

673
00:35:45.327 --> 00:35:46.762
[Miles]
Does an assault

674
00:35:46.862 --> 00:35:48.364
put Andrea at risk
if he's doing this to negotiate?

675
00:35:48.797 --> 00:35:50.866
Clegg knows
he's crossed the Rubicon.

676
00:35:50.966 --> 00:35:52.668
He is ready to go out
on his shield.

677
00:35:52.768 --> 00:35:54.002
Making himself a martyr

678
00:35:54.135 --> 00:35:56.203
certainly helps gain sympathy
for his son.

679
00:35:56.204 --> 00:35:59.007
I'm happy to oblige him.

680
00:36:01.710 --> 00:36:04.346
You know. I've been teammates
with Andrea for months now.

681
00:36:04.480 --> 00:36:07.349
I don't even know who to notify
as her next of kin.

682
00:36:09.284 --> 00:36:11.420
I think she said her mom
was back in New York.

683
00:36:12.988 --> 00:36:17.158
Right now. we're all
the family she's got.

684
00:36:17.258 --> 00:36:19.094
so let's get her home.

685
00:36:24.065 --> 00:36:25.701
[door opens]

686
00:36:25.801 --> 00:36:28.870
♪ suspenseful. dramatic music ♪

687
00:36:28.970 --> 00:36:30.105
[grunts]

688
00:36:36.578 --> 00:36:37.913
[zip ties tightening]

689
00:36:45.053 --> 00:36:46.422
[heavy door closes]

690
00:36:49.691 --> 00:36:51.527
[Andrea]
What is this?

691
00:36:52.728 --> 00:36:54.830
A man standing his ground.

692
00:37:08.243 --> 00:37:10.779
This isn't a negotiation.

693
00:37:12.681 --> 00:37:17.252
Bit by bit. I've watched
the life sucked from this land

694
00:37:17.352 --> 00:37:21.590
by faraway bureaucrats
who care nothing for it.

695
00:37:22.390 --> 00:37:24.726
I've seen the blood of my kin

696
00:37:24.826 --> 00:37:27.228
spilled by their puppets.

697
00:37:28.597 --> 00:37:32.868
You all take and take and take

698
00:37:32.968 --> 00:37:36.237
till there's nothing left
but a desert.

699
00:37:37.072 --> 00:37:39.374
It has been too dry

700
00:37:39.475 --> 00:37:42.778
for too long around here.

701
00:37:53.689 --> 00:37:55.857
And what are you in all that?

702
00:37:59.961 --> 00:38:02.130
A spark.

703
00:38:07.002 --> 00:38:09.838
It's time to burn
the land clean.

704
00:38:17.245 --> 00:38:19.648
♪

705
00:38:19.748 --> 00:38:22.784
[engines revving]

706
00:38:23.585 --> 00:38:25.554
Why was Andrea alone
when she got grabbed?

707
00:38:26.855 --> 00:38:28.524
It was a routine run.

708
00:38:28.624 --> 00:38:30.158
I didn't know we'd be
in Clegg's crosshairs.

709
00:38:30.258 --> 00:38:32.694
Belle says you were
supposed to go with her.

710
00:38:32.828 --> 00:38:34.194
Yeah. and I would've sent you.
but you

711
00:38:34.195 --> 00:38:35.163
were more worried
about your old teammate

712
00:38:35.296 --> 00:38:36.598
than the ones you got now.

713
00:38:38.834 --> 00:38:41.035
Look. man. Roner. Double G.

714
00:38:41.036 --> 00:38:42.704
that is the third rail
in our friendship.

715
00:38:42.804 --> 00:38:44.339
but the only way Drea's
gonna get out of this

716
00:38:44.472 --> 00:38:46.842
is if we are pulling
in the same direction.

717
00:38:52.247 --> 00:38:55.551
It's eerie. though. 'cause the
last thing Drea said to me...

718
00:38:56.518 --> 00:38:58.754
...was. "Hooyah. Senior Chief."

719
00:39:01.523 --> 00:39:03.458
Garrett shows up
and here we are again.

720
00:39:03.559 --> 00:39:05.727
got another teammate
behind enemy lines.

721
00:39:07.696 --> 00:39:10.065
Let's hope this one
turns out better.

722
00:39:13.301 --> 00:39:16.938
[engines revving]

723
00:39:20.008 --> 00:39:21.877
This can't be
how Andrea goes out.

724
00:39:21.977 --> 00:39:23.210
Told you.
something good happens.

725
00:39:23.211 --> 00:39:25.581
something bad always follows.

726
00:39:28.083 --> 00:39:29.751
Coming up on the property line.

727
00:39:29.885 --> 00:39:31.452
[Kayce over comms] <i>There's an
access road a few miles past</i>

728
00:39:31.553 --> 00:39:33.554
<i>the main entrance
to the Clegg compound.</i>

729
00:39:33.555 --> 00:39:36.357
<i>- We can jock up there.</i>
- Copy that.

730
00:39:40.929 --> 00:39:42.731
[bird cawing]

731
00:39:45.100 --> 00:39:46.902
No signs of activity.

732
00:39:47.002 --> 00:39:48.737
- How far out is backup?
- Like an hour out.

733
00:39:48.837 --> 00:39:50.606
- but we can't wait for them.
- [Kayce] With any luck.

734
00:39:50.739 --> 00:39:52.808
we pull this together faster
than Clegg expected.

735
00:39:52.908 --> 00:39:54.109
Yeah. we catch them off guard.

736
00:39:54.242 --> 00:39:55.677
that's our best
tactical advantage.

737
00:39:55.777 --> 00:39:57.778
Okay. look.
we're gonna proceed on foot.

738
00:39:57.779 --> 00:39:59.180
fast and quiet.

739
00:39:59.280 --> 00:40:00.916
Belle. Miles. you're gonna take
the left flank.

740
00:40:01.049 --> 00:40:02.450
Kayce and I will take the right.
and when we get to the target.

741
00:40:02.584 --> 00:40:04.920
we're gonna clear
that main house first.

742
00:40:05.020 --> 00:40:07.087
I know we're all out for blood
right now. all right?

743
00:40:07.088 --> 00:40:08.890
But remember.
this is a hostage rescue. okay?

744
00:40:08.990 --> 00:40:11.793
So careful where you send
your rounds downrange.

745
00:40:11.893 --> 00:40:13.929
- Let's get our girl back.
- [Calvin] Let's go.

746
00:40:14.029 --> 00:40:16.297
♪ tense. dramatic music ♪

747
00:40:36.117 --> 00:40:38.286
♪

748
00:40:49.798 --> 00:40:51.800
♪

749
00:41:15.957 --> 00:41:17.625
[gunfire]

750
00:41:17.726 --> 00:41:19.194
[Calvin]
Contact front!

751
00:41:22.764 --> 00:41:24.399
Down. down. down.

752
00:41:26.935 --> 00:41:28.870
[Calvin]
We need fire on that bunker!

753
00:41:35.376 --> 00:41:37.112
Contact right!

754
00:41:37.212 --> 00:41:39.047
They were expecting us.

755
00:41:46.454 --> 00:41:48.289
Clegg went
and got himself an army.

